chunk_content: For the “test kit distributed for use by” disaggregate, you would indicate a ‘1’ in the ‘sex partner’ disaggregate for the test she planned to distribute to her sex partner, ‘1’ in the “caregiver for child’ disaggregate to account for test she planned to use to screen her biological child, and a ‘1’ in the ‘other’ disaggregate to account for the test she planned to distribute to her friend. It is understood that registers and procedures for HIVST are still relatively new in many PEPFAR partner countries and specific distribution methods (e.g., vending machines) may not always allow for collection of detailed data on self-test kit distribution. As such, the only required disaggregates for this indicator will be: 1. The type of self-testing (i.e., directly assisted vs. unassisted), and 2.
